# Skill: Margin Impact Analysis

## Purpose

Analyze how quality issues, claims, rework, concessions, scrap, warranty labor, freight, and other failure costs affect product, customer, channel, brand, or business unit margin.

This skill should help leaders understand where quality problems are eroding profitability and which improvement opportunities can protect or expand margin.

## When to Use This Skill

Use this skill when evaluating:

- Product margin erosion
- Customer profitability issues
- Quality-adjusted margin
- Claim cost impact
- Warranty exposure
- Scrap and rework cost
- Freight or replacement cost
- Customer concessions
- Margin leakage by product, brand, channel, or customer
- Cost of quality impact on profitability

## Business Objectives Supported

Margin impact analysis should connect findings to:

- Grow net sales by protecting customer trust and supporting profitable growth
- Reduce the cash conversion cycle by reducing credits, disputes, replacements, and rework
- Manage the balance sheet by reducing reserves, liabilities, and preventable cost exposure
- Reduce failure cost and margin leakage
- Prioritize improvement work based on financial return

